                 node js :  server side technology
              ......................................


                        Basic Comments
                  ..........................
            1.to create package.json=>npm init
            2.to install express=>npm i express
            3.install nodemon=>npm i -g nodemon
            4.to run the server=>node/nodemon index.js
            5.install JWT token=>npm i jsonwebtoken
            6.install mongoose=>npm install mongoose
            7.install cors=>npm i cors



                        Basic Concepts
                    ............................
            1.create a folder  
            2.create package.json
            3.create index.js file
            4.install express 
            5.import expres to index.js  
            6.create app using expres   
            7.define port no for server app  
            8.install nodemon
            9.middleware
              9.1 application specific middleware
              9.2 Router specific middleware
            10.JWT token
              10.1 token generation=>sign()
              10.2 token verify=>verify()

            11.connection b/w mongoDB and server
               11.1 install mongoose
               11.2 provide connection string using mongoose
               11.3 create model
               11.4 export model
            12.solving Asynchronous events
               12.1  promise
                 12.1.1 resolved state :then()
                 12.1.2 reject state : catch( )
            13. Cors :cross origin resourse sharing protocol
               13.1 install cors
               13.2 import cors to index.js



           * only one request has o/p on browser ie,GET request
           * To see all other req are working use thunder client(test wether req are work properly)